ion did was fix state corruption — Ralph's stale in-memory state keeps reverting stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 from `done` to `review`. This has happened 42 times now.\n\nWrite the retrospective to _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-28.md. If a retro for today already exists, append to it with a `---` separator and timestamp.\n\nFocus on:\n1. The waste — 42 no-op sessions fixing the same corruption\n2. The root cause — Ralph overwrites sprint-state.json with stale state\n3. The fix needed — Ralph must be stopped or the state overwrite bug must be fixed\n4. Cost analysis from the stats\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.","agentId":"a9b31807d4de05238","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Session 58 retrospective appended to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-28.md`.\n\nKey findings:\n\n- **$733.86 total sprint cost**, up $2.02 from session 57\n- **42 consecutive no-op sessions** fixing identical state corruption (stories 16-5 through 16-8)\n- **~$90-126 wasted** on no-op sessions alone (12-17% of total cost)\n- **~$114-150 total waste** when including the `1-1-foo` phantom story ($24.35) -- up to 20% of the sprint budget\n- **Root cause unchanged:** Ralph writes stale in-memory state to `sprint-state.json`, reverting 4 completed stories. `ralph/status.json` still shows `stories_completed: 70`, `stories_remaining: 4`.\n- **The only fix is stopping Ralph.** 42 retros saying \"STOP RALPH\" in markdown have not stopped Ralph. The process needs to be killed or the scheduler disabled."}],"totalDurationMs":61954,"totalTokens":41910,"totalToolUseCount":9,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2423,"cache_read_input_tokens":39216,"output_tokens":270,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{